I love this! It's cute, it has an edge of comedy, and it is pretty clever retake of Sigurros/239 kinda stuff but with less existential horror that ended up making it kinda too big to really care about.

Nonetheless, this article scared the shit out of me.

It reminded me how much environment shapes a child's, and even an adult's, perception of the world. I had always been particularly easy to sway as a kid, I can't count how many times I cried to my parents for snacks I saw on television and I'm sure I at least doubled their electric bills by insisting that I won't eat cold rice and forcing them to keep our rice warm 24/7. To even consider that the same 

+1, and not only because it's a gift.







